==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weet-weet
<hw>Weet"-weet`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from
its piping cry when disturbed.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>The common European sandpiper.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
chaffinch.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weet-weet</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Weet-weet
<hw>Weet"-weet`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native name in
Victoria.]</ety> <def>A throwing toy, or implement, of the Australian
aborigines, consisting of a cigar-shaped stick fastened at one end to a
flexible twig. It weighs in all about two ounces, and is about two feet
long.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weever</ent>⟦br⟧
